content:
Modifying a propulsion system to overcome space-time anomalies like black holes and creating an intuitive wearable glove interface involves advanced theoretical physics and human-computer interaction design. Here is a conceptual JSON format that outlines the required modifications:

```json
{
  "propulsionSystem": {
    "propulsionType": "Warp Drive",
    "features": [
      {
        "featureName": "Space-Time Distortion Control",
        "description": "Allows manipulation of space-time fabric to avoid anomalies.",
        "technology": [
          {
            "techName": "Artificial Gravity Wells",
            "function": "Generate localized gravity wells to steer the spacecraft."
          },
          {
            "techName": "Quantum Tunneling",
            "function": "Enable transitions through space-time discontinuities."
          },
          {
            "techName": "Negative Energy Fields",
            "function": "Use negative energy to stabilize space-time around black holes."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "featureName": "Anomaly Detection System",
        "description": "Detects and analyzes space-time anomalies in real-time.",
        "technology": [
          {
            "techName": "Gravitational Wave Sensors",
            "function": "Monitor gravitational disturbances indicative of anomalies."
          },
          {
            "techName": "Quantum Entanglement Communication",
            "function": "Instantaneous data relay for anomaly detection."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "wearableGloveInterface": {
    "designPrinciples": [
      "Ergonomic Design",
      "Intuitive Interaction",
      "Feedback Sensitivity"
    ],
    "features": [
      {
        "featureName": "Haptic Feedback",
        "description": "Provides tactile responses to user inputs.",
        "technology": [
          {
            "techName": "Micro-Actuators",
            "function": "Deliver precise tactile sensations."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "featureName": "Gesture Recognition",
        "description": "Interprets hand movements as input commands.",
        "technology": [
          {
            "techName": "Motion Sensors",
            "function": "Track hand and finger movements."
          },
          {
            "techName": "Machine Learning Algorithms",
            "function": "Enhances recognition accuracy over time."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "featureName": "User Interface Customization",
        "description": "Allows users to tailor the interface according to preferences.",
        "technology": [
          {
            "techName": "AI-driven Personalization",
            "function": "Adapts interface based on usage patterns."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
```

This JSON structure outlines a theoretical propulsion system and wearable glove interface design. The propulsion system involves speculative technologies like warp drives and negative energy, reflecting current scientific hypotheses rather than proven technologies. The glove interface focuses on usability and adaptability, emphasizing interaction ease and customization.
